<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by STOPAIDS</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">STOPAIDS </span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Introduction</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">STOPAIDS is the network of 80 UK agencies working since 1986 to secure an effective global response to HIV and AIDS.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We endorse the submission from the Bond Disability</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and Development Working Group and make a few simple points bringing the perspective of a network focused on HIV and AIDS.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Context</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Disabled people’s access to information and programmes addressing HIV and AIDS is often inadequate. This flows from a numbe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">r of barriers and including: </span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">prevailing cultural norms which assume that disabled people do not have sexual identities and/or are not vulnerable to sexual violence which puts them at risk of HIV infection;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the inability of mainstream development agencies</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to reach out to and communicate effectively with disabled people;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the reluctance of influential agencies such as DFID to fully prioritise the rights of disabled people.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Additionally, and for the first time since the start of the HIV epidemic 32 years ago, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">10% of the adult population living with HIV in low- and middle-income countries is aged 50 or older</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. This brings a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">n increased need to ensure equitable and sustainable a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ccess to affordable, innovative medicines in order to off-set the increased risks of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">more chronic illnesses and disability</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Recommendations</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In its recent publication, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Towards Zero Infections – Two Years On</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">DFID identifies disabled people as being </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">’hard to reach’ group. We therefore </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">recommend that DFID articulate clear goals for how it will use its financial and political influence to advance the position of disabled people in the context of the HIV epidemic in order to (a) increase disabled peopl</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e’s access to prevention, treatment, care and support and (b) reduce people’s vulnerability to disability resulting from a lack of e</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">quitable and sustainable access to affordable, innovative medicines</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Drawing on the programmatic experience of our members </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">we specifically recommend:</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">building the capacity of disabled people’s organisations to provide information on HIV/AIDS;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">encouraging the disaggregation of data in all reporting on prevention, treatment and care and support programmes;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">recognising</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the vulnerability of disabled people, and disabled women and girls in particular, to sexual violence which increases their vulnerability to HIV and AIDS;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ensur</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> that health facilities are physically and linguistically accessible for disabled people, extending Lynne Featherstone</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s recent commitment that all new school funded by DFID would be accessible to CWD and extending this to health centres;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">recognis</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ing the a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">dditional stigma and poverty facing disabled people who are also HIV positive.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:15.6pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> See UNAIDS </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">HIV and Aging </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">report, November 2013 </span><a href="http://www.unaids.org/en/media/unaids/contentassets/documents/unaidspublication/2013/20131101_JC2563_hiv-and-aging_en.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.unaids.org/en/media/unaids/contentassets/documents/unaidspublication/2013/20131101_JC2563_hiv-and-aging_en.pdf</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://stopaids.org.uk/our-actions/access-to-medicines/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://stopaids.org.uk/our-actions/access-to-medicines/</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a href="http://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/Towards%2520zero%2520infections%2520two%2520years%2520on_0.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/Towards%20zero%20infections%20two%20years%20on_0.pdf</span></a></p></body></html>